column5: I've been searching online for information about Ontario steelhead stocking data but have been unable to find anything current.  What I would like to see is a year by year list of the numbers of Steelhead stocked per river.  I know that the info is out there. Anyone have a link?

in the documents below scroll to the 3rd or 4th page and they list body of water stocked   here is brown trout 2000  http://www.mnr.gov.on.ca/226914.pdf  here is brown trout 2001  http://www.mnr.gov.on.ca/226916.pdf  here is 2006 list all  http://www.mnr.gov.on.ca/en/Business/LetsF...age/200357.html  here is 2005 listy all  http://www.mnr.gov.on.ca/en/Business/LetsF...age/200356.html  here is 2004 list all  http://www.mnr.gov.on.ca/en/Business/LetsF...age/200355.html  here is 2003 list all  http://www.mnr.gov.on.ca/en/Business/LetsF...age/200354.html  here is 2002 list all  http://www.mnr.gov.on.ca/en/Business/LetsF...age/200353.html  here is 2001 list all  http://www.mnr.gov.on.ca/en/Business/LetsF...age/200352.html  here is musky stocking in the past for the kawarthas  http://www.mnr.gov.on.ca/226917.pdf
This is what you're after.  Great dbase, #'s, clips, locations, even strain that was stocked.  http://www.glfc.org/fishstocking/index.htm
